[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Judicial review[bold]Overview 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Implications for human r
[normal]ights
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“Where an infringement of an 
[normal]individual's human rights has occurred, the concern will usually be to bring the infringement to an end and any question of compensation will be of secondary, if any, importance. This is reflected in the fact that, when it is necessary to resort to the cou
[normal]rts to uphold and protect human rights
[normal], the remedies that are most frequently sought are the orders which are the descendants of the historic prerogative orders or declaratory judgments[bold]. The orders enable the court to order a public body to refrain from or
[normal] to take action, or to quash an offending administrative decision of a public body.”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Disproportionate i
[normal]mpact
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]An application for permission carries a relatively high risk of initial failure. Even where a claim is meritorious it is often necessary to persist to an oral hearing or further to obtain permission. 
[normal]For example, while 
[normal]Wood v Commissioner of Police
[normal] is now
[normal] a leading case on privacy and police records, p
[normal]ermission
[normal] for judicial review
[normal] was only granted on appeal. 
[normal] 
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Judicial review claims are “front loaded” in 
[normal]that most of the work from the c
[normal]laimant’s perspective must be done at the stage of brin
[normal]g
[normal]ing the claim. Practitioners therefore have to invest a large amount of time, cost and effort for which they may not get paid. This is increased still further if they have to proceed to an oral hearing or appeal. 
[normal]c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Applications for permission are difficult 
[normal]to predict and there is much variability among judges
[normal], and
[normal]d)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Many cases settle on beneficial terms after issue but before permission. It is not possible to tell how these are reflected in the statistics. Under the proposals these cases would not be paid for 
[normal]except on a discretionary basis.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
