[normal]a)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Instead of making sensible and reasoned assessments (i.e. that the prospects cannot be precisely measured) where the pr
[normal]ospects are genuinely unclear, it will be necessary to err on the side of caution and assess at 51% where (as in all such cases presently falling into the scheme) something really important is at stake
[normal]b)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Decisions by the Director of Legal Aid which put the p
[normal]rospects of success to be just less than 50% will lead to more appeals to Adjudicators
[normal],
[normal] therefore tying up additional resources, and
[normal]c)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]More applications will be made for legal aid at the investigatory level to enable a more precise assessment of prospects 
[normal]of
[normal] success, 
[normal]building in additional cost and, often more importantly, delay.
